  "local_port": 45918,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I deleted my friend ID from WeChat. How do I find it again?",
  "response": "If you deleted your friend's ID from WeChat and want to find it again, here are some steps you can try:\n\n### 1. **Check Your Chat History**\n   - If you had conversations with the friend before deleting them, you can still access the chat history.\n   - Open WeChat and go to the \"Chats\" tab.\n   - Scroll to find the chat with the friend. Their name or ID should still be visible there.\n\n### 2. **Search for Their Phone Number or WeChat ID**\n   - If you know their phone number or WeChat ID, you can search for them again:\n     - Go to **Contacts** > **Add Contacts**.\n     - Enter their phone number or WeChat ID in the search bar.\n\n### 3. **Check Mutual Friends**\n   - If you have mutual friends, you can ask them to share the friend's ID or profile with you.\n\n### 4. **Look in Your Moments**\n   - If you interacted with their posts in your Moments, their profile might still be accessible there:\n     - Go to **Discover** > **Moments**.\n     - Look for past posts or comments from them.\n\n### 5. **Check Your WeChat Backup (if enabled)**\n   - If you have backed up your WeChat data, you might be able to restore your contacts:\n     - Go to **Me** > **Settings** > **Chat** > **Backup & Migration**.\n     - Restore from your backup if available.\n\n### 6. **Ask Them Directly**\n   - If none of the above works, you can reach out to the friend through another platform (e.g., phone call, email) and ask for their WeChat ID.\n\n### 7. **Check Group Chats**\n   - If you and your friend were part of the same WeChat group, you can find them in the group members list:\n     - Open the group chat, tap on the group name, and scroll through the members.\n\nIf you didn\u2019t save their contact information or backup your data, it might be challenging to retrieve their ID. Make sure to save important contacts in the future!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
